There is an emergency closure of US 2 northeast of Wenatchee from MP 142 to MP 144 just west of Waterville due to a rock slide in Pine Canyon. There is no detour available and motorists are encouraged to take an alternate route. This will be an extended closure and there is currently no estimated date for reopening. US 2 Pine Canyon Emergency Slide Repairs #MS8489County: Douglas Highway: US 2 Region: North CentralLocation: MP 143 (Orondo to Waterville)Description: A contractor is removing unstable rock repairing anchors and netting and removing debris from a rockslide that occurred in February.Work schedule: US 2 Pine Canyon is currently closed to traffic between Orondo and Waterville. There are no official detours but alternative routes for non-freight travel are available on McNeil Canyon Rd. and Badger Mountain Rd. The road is scheduled to be reopened no later than March 25.Contact: Project Engineer James Reynolds 509-667-2861
